;        cross-attention KV cache for greedy decode (transformer-generate-cached.fk, identical ids). (3)
;        BPE merge core proven against the REAL whisper tokenizer (bpe-tokenizer.fk: " the"→264,
;        " tokenizer"→[14862,6545], exact). Remaining to an end-to-end transcript: assemble the pieces at
;        real width via JIT, learned decoder positionals, byte-map + regex word-split carriers, exact-erf gelu.]
;        [SPEEDUP MEASURED via the BOOTSTRAP-ORACLE (the 33s interpreter block is a walker cost, not a real
;        one): the Form matvec EMITTER (jit-tensor-emit.fk jte-matvec-rust) → rustc-cdylib ORACLE runs a
;        384×384 matvec in ~0.1ms and 1280×1280 (whisper-large width) in ~1.6ms, bit-exact vs numpy (the
;        j-DOWN fold). rustc here is the speed REFERENCE, not the sovereign lane — the native target is
;        form-asm BYTES over ll-buffer (fa-ldr-d/fa-str-d/fa-fmul/fa-fadd, four-way), which earns the same
;        bit-exact result with rustc/clang dropped by the byte-identity gate.
